n.泻药 【英】 n.泻药(a purging medicine; cathartic) 无 【记】purge 净化，净化肚子用泻药 purgative (adj.)  late 14c., from Old French purgatif (14c.) and directly from Late Latin purgativus, from purgat-, past participle stem of Latin purgare (see purge (v.)). The noun is attested from early 15c. (Old English medical texts have clænsungdrenc).
